22:29.231 --> 22:31.631
Hey, it's Gerry at Enniskerry Limo.
Leave a message.

22:38.741 --> 22:40.675
[PHONE RINGS]

22:40.943 --> 22:42.103
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

22:42.278 --> 22:45.042
PATRICIA [OVER ANSWERING MACHINE]:
Holly? It's Mom. Are you all right?

22:45.214 --> 22:46.841
Are you showering? Don't make me worry.

22:47.016 --> 22:48.847
SHARON:
I'm worried you're not calling me back.

22:49.018 --> 22:52.715
I know it's hard, honey, but don't lock
yourself in. It's been over a week.

22:52.888 --> 22:54.515
- I'm here, okay?
DENISE: Hey, it's Denise.

22:54.690 --> 22:57.853
Listen, I buzzed your apartment.
Nobody's heard from you.

22:58.027 --> 23:01.463
Where are you? All right, call somebody.
I love you.

23:01.630 --> 23:03.825
[OVER TV]
I'll make him pay for it. I will.

23:03.999 --> 23:05.626
Whatever you might do,
I can do more...

23:05.801 --> 23:07.928
...because I know how to fight
better than you.

23:08.904 --> 23:11.634
Why can't I be Bette Davis?

23:13.442 --> 23:15.171
GERRY'S VOICE:
All right? I mean, the job...

23:15.344 --> 23:17.369
...makes you cranky
at home every bloody day anyway.

23:17.546 --> 23:19.138
You wanna have a baby? Let's do it.

23:19.315 --> 23:22.250
HOLLY: See? I hate when you do that.
GERRY: Hah. Do what?

23:22.418 --> 23:23.851
HOLLY:
Let's have a baby. La-la-la!

23:24.019 --> 23:26.249
In a five-floor walkup
we can barely move in.

23:26.422 --> 23:29.653
You can't act like everything's just
gonna work out by itself, Gerry.

23:29.825 --> 23:32.885
Why do I have to be the responsible
grownup who worries?

23:33.062 --> 23:34.791
[OVER TV]
If you're killed, I'll be free.

23:34.964 --> 23:36.761
If I'm killed, it really doesn't matter.

23:36.932 --> 23:39.162
If we both die, good riddance!

23:39.335 --> 23:41.929
JOHN ELDREDGE:
Go ahead, crash it. Crash it!

23:46.108 --> 23:47.234
[SIGHS]

23:47.409 --> 23:48.569
[TV CLICKS OFF]

23:48.744 --> 23:51.269
Gerry, get the light.

23:51.447 --> 23:53.506
It's your turn.

23:54.717 --> 23:56.446
Mmm.

24:12.034 --> 24:14.025
[GUITAR PLAYING]

24:18.674 --> 24:21.973
GERRY [SINGING]:
I just want to see you

24:22.144 --> 24:24.476
When you're all alone

24:25.581 --> 24:30.177
I just want to catch you if I can

24:32.555 --> 24:39.154
I just want to be there
When the morning light explodes

24:39.495 --> 24:44.455
On your face it radiates
I can't escape

24:44.633 --> 24:47.500
I love you till the end

24:48.270 --> 24:51.000
- Do all Irishmen sing?
- Heh.

24:51.507 --> 24:54.271
I'll love you till the end

24:54.476 --> 24:57.502
Ah. Only the really well-hung ones.

24:58.180 --> 25:01.206
I can't fall asleep alone.

25:01.383 --> 25:03.317
I'm right here, baby.

25:03.485 --> 25:06.079
I had a terrible dream.

25:06.855 --> 25:08.948
Don't tell me.

25:10.960 --> 25:15.329
Gerry, I don't wanna go back to work.

25:15.497 --> 25:19.263
- What should I do?
- Quit.

25:19.835 --> 25:21.530
Stay here with me.

25:21.704 --> 25:23.467
[MOANS]

25:28.844 --> 25:31.176
I don't have a plan, Gerry.

25:31.347 --> 25:35.078
That's okay, luv,
your plans never work out anyway.

25:35.818 --> 25:37.217
Hmm.

25:37.453 --> 25:39.785
That's true.

25:40.756 --> 25:44.192
[JUD Y GARLAND SINGING
"THE MAN THAT GOT AWAY" OVER TV]

25:53.969 --> 25:58.133
HOLLY [SINGING ALONG]:
And all because of the man

25:58.307 --> 26:04.439
That got away

26:04.613 --> 26:10.779
No more his eager call

26:10.953 --> 26:17.358
The writing's on the wall

26:17.660 --> 26:23.758
The dreams you dreamed
Have all

26:23.932 --> 26:28.960
Gone astray

26:30.773 --> 26:37.235
The man that won you
Has run off and undone you

26:37.413 --> 26:43.579
That great beginning
Has seen a final inning

26:44.153 --> 26:47.384
Don't know what happened

26:47.556 --> 26:54.394
It's all a crazy game

26:54.997 --> 27:00.993
No more that all-time thrill

27:01.170 --> 27:03.934
For you've been

27:04.106 --> 27:07.473
Through the mill

27:07.643 --> 27:11.773
And never a new love

27:11.947 --> 27:18.682
Will be the same

27:19.121 --> 27:23.455
Good riddance, goodbye...

27:27.463 --> 27:28.987
[TV CLICKS OFF]

27:32.568 --> 27:35.264
CIARA:
Whoo!

27:36.805 --> 27:38.966
ALL:
Happy birthday!

27:39.241 --> 27:40.401
[BOTH BLOW PARTY HORN]

27:40.642 --> 27:42.371
You're 30!

27:42.544 --> 27:44.273
Hey, Holly...

27:44.446 --> 27:46.641
...these were falling out of your mailbox.

27:47.883 --> 27:49.077
What is that smell?

27:49.251 --> 27:52.152
I wasn't expecting company.
Mom, don't clean.

27:52.321 --> 27:56.485
- I'm not. I'll just organize the garbage.
- We did try to call first.

27:56.658 --> 27:59.126
- Are you drunk?
- No.

27:59.294 --> 28:01.694
- Do you wanna be?
- Ciara.

28:01.864 --> 28:03.388
What happened to your head?

28:03.932 --> 28:04.921
Pimple.

28:05.100 --> 28:07.660
- You're not showering?
- You always squeeze it too hard.

28:07.836 --> 28:09.736
- What is that smell?
- It's me, all right?

28:09.905 --> 28:12.465
Hey, hey, hey. Don't be like that.

28:12.875 --> 28:16.743
- Like what?
- Like the only lonely widow in Gotham City.

28:16.912 --> 28:19.938
I'm just... exhausted.

28:20.115 --> 28:22.743
Yeah, well, what are you doing,
two shows a night?

28:23.252 --> 28:24.583
[STIFLED CHUCKLE]

28:25.420 --> 28:28.150
You know, if you want us to leave,
that's fine...

28:28.323 --> 28:31.622
...but you do know that at some point,
this all has to stop.

28:33.595 --> 28:35.358
All right.

28:36.131 --> 28:39.897
Just give me a second, okay?
I'll get cleaned up.

28:40.636 --> 28:44.367
- Okay, troops, let's sweep the area.
- Yes.

28:45.941 --> 28:48.068
I haven't called the office. Are they mad?

28:48.243 --> 28:51.940
Nah. There's no rush.

28:52.114 --> 28:56.949
Even Larry said, "Take all the time you
need. The job is there when you're ready."

28:57.119 --> 28:58.313
That was nice of him.

28:58.487 --> 29:00.978
- He's an asshole.
- He's still an asshole.

29:01.290 --> 29:05.454
Do you think it'll be all right
if I stop my life right here?

29:05.627 --> 29:10.064
Become the Miss Havisham
of the Lower East Side.

29:10.232 --> 29:12.393
Never leave my apartment till I'm old.

29:12.568 --> 29:14.695
- Sit in my wedding dress.
- Which you never had.

29:14.870 --> 29:17.703
- With an old piece of wedding cake.
- Which you never had.

29:18.407 --> 29:19.999
You gotta be rich to be insane, Hol.

29:20.175 --> 29:21.164
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

29:21.343 --> 29:23.504
Losing your mind
is not a luxury for the middle class.

29:23.679 --> 29:25.806
CIARA: I'll get it.
- That's so not fair.

29:26.315 --> 29:28.408
No, it's not.

29:29.284 --> 29:31.411
Holly? Something's been delivered for you.

29:42.331 --> 29:43.491
What is this?

29:46.001 --> 29:49.698
- I don't understand. Did you do this?
- No.

29:50.539 --> 29:51.597
JOHN:
Wait a minute.

30:02.284 --> 30:06.744
- John, tell me the truth. Did you do this?
- No. I did nothing, I swear.

30:18.600 --> 30:20.591
[MUSIC PLAYING]

30:21.503 --> 30:24.404
GERRY [OVER TAPE RECORDER]:
Hey, baby. Surprise.

30:24.573 --> 30:27.269
I know this probably feels
a little bit morbid...

30:27.442 --> 30:30.104
...but I just hate the idea
that I'm not gonna be there...

30:30.279 --> 30:33.908
...to see you freak out over turning 30.
I mean, it kills me not to be there.

30:34.082 --> 30:36.175
Heh-heh. That's funny.

30:36.351 --> 30:39.252
- No, it's not.
- Okay. No, it's not.

30:39.721 --> 30:44.317
You're gonna be so impressed.
I have a plan, baby. Can you believe it?

30:44.493 --> 30:48.554
I've written you letters. Letters that will be
coming to you all sorts of ways.

30:48.730 --> 30:52.427
I waited till your birthday. I figured
you weren't stepping out of the house...

30:52.601 --> 30:55.570
...for a while. Letter number one
will be arriving tomorrow.

30:56.038 --> 30:58.905
Now, you must do what I say, okay?

30:59.074 --> 31:00.905
Okay?

31:01.209 --> 31:03.541
Don't try to figure out
how the letters are coming.

31:03.712 --> 31:08.149
It's too brilliant and it'll ruin my plan.
Just go along with me on this.

31:08.317 --> 31:12.777
Because the thing is,
I just can't say goodbye yet.

31:13.822 --> 31:15.790
So for starters...

31:15.958 --> 31:19.257
...I want you to get dolled up,
and just go out and celebrate tonight.

31:19.428 --> 31:20.986
Go out with your girlies.

31:21.163 --> 31:26.100
I hereby free you from a party with
your family, especially your mom.

31:26.368 --> 31:28.996
Oh, man, your mom's there, isn't she?

31:29.171 --> 31:31.298
Mm. Shit.

31:31.506 --> 31:33.269
Sorry, Patricia.

31:33.442 --> 31:34.966
It isn't that I don't love you...

31:35.143 --> 31:38.704
...but she needs to get a little crazy.
So have a slice of the bloody cake...

31:38.880 --> 31:41.178
...put on your dress
and get out of the apartment.

31:41.350 --> 31:43.113
- Denise, make a plan.
- I'm on it!

31:43.285 --> 31:46.277
- I'll help.
- Just leave me with John, okay?

31:46.455 --> 31:50.084
And know that wherever I am,
I'm missing you.

31:50.993 --> 31:52.824
Happy birthday.

31:53.261 --> 31:54.558
I love you.

31:58.700 --> 32:00.531
[WHOOPING, CHATTERING]

32:03.638 --> 32:05.697
- Come on.
- Look, it's a private gay club.

32:05.874 --> 32:09.332
Yes, but we are on the list.
My colorist called and he's gay.

32:09.511 --> 32:11.843
Gay colorist in New York?
Like sand on the beach.

32:12.014 --> 32:14.482
Listen, Crystal. Don't mess with her.

32:14.649 --> 32:16.640
- He's a very good colorist.
- Uh-huh.

32:16.818 --> 32:20.549
And she's the princess of Finland.

32:20.956 --> 32:25.052
And she's here on matters
of critical political importance.

32:25.227 --> 32:28.754
And she's here to extend
the hand of friendship from Finland...

32:28.930 --> 32:30.488
...to homosexuals...
MAN: That's us!

32:30.665 --> 32:32.565
...throughout the tri-city area.

32:32.734 --> 32:34.497
[MEN WHOOPING]

32:34.836 --> 32:36.827
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

32:40.375 --> 32:41.899
What?

32:42.077 --> 32:44.068
[CROWD CHEERING]

32:46.782 --> 32:48.374
HOLLY:
Thanks.

32:51.253 --> 32:52.720
Great. You're fired.

32:52.888 --> 32:54.287
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

32:54.456 --> 32:56.447
[CROWD CHEERING]

33:01.029 --> 33:04.863
Okay. "Snaps" is the name of the game.
The name of the game is "Snaps."

33:05.033 --> 33:06.557
Make sure you pay attention.

33:06.735 --> 33:07.724
[SNAPS]

33:07.903 --> 33:08.892
Ready?

33:09.071 --> 33:11.972
[SNAPS THREE TIMES]

33:12.140 --> 33:13.835
Have you got it?

33:14.009 --> 33:14.998
Mariah Carey?

33:15.177 --> 33:17.168
[ALL CHEER]

33:17.479 --> 33:18.468
I don't get it.

33:18.747 --> 33:20.510
- Paul.
- God, he's been dead, like what?

33:20.682 --> 33:22.172
- Fifteen years.
- Unbelievable.

33:22.350 --> 33:24.784
- Can you believe that?
- You remember Steve?

33:24.953 --> 33:27.888
Steve was so sweet.
He was a good guy.

33:28.056 --> 33:30.923
- Honey, don't be so Miss Doom and Gloom.
- You'll be fine.

33:31.093 --> 33:32.924
Yeah, don't worry about it.

33:33.428 --> 33:34.986
CIARA:
"Snaps" is the name of the game.

33:35.163 --> 33:37.222
The name of the game is "Snaps."

33:37.399 --> 33:38.491
- Do you hear me?
- Yeah.

33:38.667 --> 33:39.895
[SNAPS TWICE]

33:40.068 --> 33:43.060
Ready? Keep looking.

33:43.572 --> 33:44.766
PATRICIA AND JOHN:
Derek Jeter!

33:44.940 --> 33:47.340
- Come on. No.
- How?

33:47.509 --> 33:48.669
SHARON:
This is a stupid game.

33:48.844 --> 33:50.778
[WOMEN LAUGHING, CHATTERING]

33:55.150 --> 33:56.811
Sorry.

33:57.219 --> 33:58.208
What are you doing?

33:58.386 --> 34:00.854
Trying to figure out
why God killed my husband.

34:01.022 --> 34:03.616
Well, if you need any help with that,
let me know.

34:09.563 --> 34:11.690
- Ow!
- Sorry. Heh.

34:13.235 --> 34:15.226
- Daniel?
- Yeah.

34:15.637 --> 34:18.572
So why do you think...?

34:18.739 --> 34:20.503
Your husband died?

34:20.675 --> 34:22.699
Maybe you're being punished
for something.

34:22.878 --> 34:25.072
- What?
- Being too happy? Too beautiful?

34:25.246 --> 34:27.340
I don't know.
God can be a pretty jealous guy.

34:27.516 --> 34:30.679
I don't believe that. I've never been
too happy. I'm not too beautiful.

34:30.851 --> 34:32.478
I think you're hot.

34:36.525 --> 34:38.583
Sorry, I have a syndrome.

34:38.760 --> 34:42.025
I don't really have a filter.
I don't pick up on social cues.

34:42.197 --> 34:43.630
You mean you're rude?

34:43.797 --> 34:46.824
Yeah, but now it's a disease
I can take medication for.

34:47.268 --> 34:49.134
They have pills for rudeness?

34:49.304 --> 34:52.330
I know. And they can't figure out
the Middle East. Go figure.

34:52.507 --> 34:54.498
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

34:55.143 --> 34:58.408
Hey, you're Irish.
Maybe it's an Irish curse or something.

34:58.580 --> 35:00.775
Well, Gerry and I did love the Yankees...

35:00.949 --> 35:03.213
...which was pretty much
against our religion.

35:03.385 --> 35:04.545
Well, there you go.

35:04.719 --> 35:09.019
That explains a lot, actually. I love the
Yankees too, and I lost my fiancée last year.

35:09.558 --> 35:10.547
Really?

35:10.725 --> 35:14.126
Yeah, she slept with my best friend.
She left me.

35:14.296 --> 35:15.354
Oh...

35:15.597 --> 35:17.531
My best friend was a woman.

35:17.699 --> 35:18.688
Oh.

35:18.867 --> 35:22.200
Her last words to me were, "I'd still
be with you if you weren't a man."

35:22.370 --> 35:23.701
And I'm like:

35:23.872 --> 35:28.206
"Well, castrating me is definitely the first
step toward achieving that particular goal."

35:28.476 --> 35:30.307
It's still my fault. I introduced them.

35:30.478 --> 35:33.936
I always had this fantasy about making love
to two women at the same time.

35:34.115 --> 35:37.573
Except in my fantasy, I was still
in the bed for the second and third time.

35:37.752 --> 35:39.811
- Sorry.
- Then this'll make you feel great.

35:39.988 --> 35:43.685
The best friend that my ex-fiancée slept
with was my ex-ex-fiancée...

35:43.858 --> 35:47.692
...and she was my business partner, and
we started the business with my money.

35:47.862 --> 35:52.526
So I ended up losing the business,
my partner and my fiancée.

35:52.968 --> 35:55.129
How'd you get over that?

35:56.238 --> 36:00.265
I went through, like,
a major hooker phase all year.

36:00.442 --> 36:01.739
But that didn't help.

36:01.910 --> 36:04.879
No, it helped a lot.
I just started to run out of money.

36:05.046 --> 36:07.344
It's actually a lot cheaper to date.

36:08.583 --> 36:12.485
Do you think that you're gonna ever find
another woman to love?

36:13.421 --> 36:14.786
No.

36:14.956 --> 36:19.086
No, I think I repel
the women that I want the most.

36:20.262 --> 36:21.456
That's not true.

36:22.530 --> 36:23.792
No?

36:24.766 --> 36:26.757
[VOMITING]

36:29.537 --> 36:31.095
No?

37:01.002 --> 37:02.629
HOLLY:
Thank you, Daniel.

37:10.679 --> 37:13.011
You can start closing up downstairs.

37:16.351 --> 37:17.818
Right.

37:25.627 --> 37:26.924
[MOANS]

37:39.274 --> 37:41.174
[CELL PHONE RINGTONE
PLAYING LOUDLY]

37:51.353 --> 37:52.581
What do you want?

37:53.021 --> 37:55.615
- Oh, good. A friendly voice.
HOLLY [OVER PHONE]: Oh.

37:55.990 --> 37:57.389
What happened last night?

37:57.559 --> 37:59.993
Lemon drops and tequila, my friend.

38:00.161 --> 38:03.722
The moment where a 30-year-old body
does not recover quite as fast...

38:03.898 --> 38:05.490
...as a 29-year-old body.

38:05.667 --> 38:07.362
Stop screaming at me.

38:07.736 --> 38:10.227
- Are you working?
- Hell, no.

38:10.405 --> 38:13.841
But I told him we're gonna start next week.
We'll go out starting Monday.

38:14.042 --> 38:18.240
- Is that okay?
- No, I was planning on...

38:18.413 --> 38:20.779
...staying in bed and dying today.

38:20.949 --> 38:21.938
[CHUCKLES]

38:22.117 --> 38:23.550
Well, you can't.

38:23.718 --> 38:26.380
You gotta go check the mailbox,
remember?

38:26.554 --> 38:28.886
Call me immediately.

38:51.212 --> 38:53.908
GERRY: Save yourself bruises
and buy yourself a bedside lamp.

38:54.582 --> 38:57.847
And remember, a disco diva
must look her best.

38:58.019 --> 39:01.853
Go buy yourself a knock-out outfit. You'll
need it for when my next letter comes.

39:02.023 --> 39:03.251
Need it for what?

39:03.425 --> 39:06.758
And I know you hate your job,
but I'll help.

39:06.928 --> 39:10.227
Look for a sign. You'll know what to do.

39:13.835 --> 39:16.633
P.S. I love you.

39:16.805 --> 39:18.796
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKING ON AND OFF]

40:11.559 --> 40:14.187
HOLLY [WHISPERING]:
I still know you're around.

40:14.796 --> 40:17.264
You're still here, aren't you?

40:20.301 --> 40:21.666
MAN:
So who lived here before?

40:21.836 --> 40:25.567
A family. They're having another baby.
So do you have any children?

40:25.740 --> 40:28.641
Three. Girls. Teenagers.

40:28.810 --> 40:30.004
That's nice.

40:30.311 --> 40:31.505
Uh-huh.

40:31.713 --> 40:34.204
Ted, Sharon says there's
another offer on the table...

40:34.382 --> 40:36.213
...and we have to move on this.

40:36.384 --> 40:39.251
SHARON: I think if you offer another
hundred grand, they'll back down.

40:39.420 --> 40:41.285
Well, maybe we should talk about it.

40:41.456 --> 40:43.788
We don't have time, Ted.
We have to tell her today.

40:43.958 --> 40:45.118
We didn't wanna go over...

40:45.293 --> 40:47.955
I know, but we love this apartment,
and it is what it is.

40:48.162 --> 40:50.722
There's nothing else.
This is what an apartment costs.

40:50.899 --> 40:53.299
- We're already beyond our cap.
- We'll make it work...

40:53.468 --> 40:56.335
- Think about another area.
- I am not living in Brooklyn.

40:56.504 --> 40:58.062
- Will you listen to him?
BOTH: What?

40:58.239 --> 40:59.900
He's obviously worried about this.

41:00.074 --> 41:01.871
- Look at him. He's pale.
- Hol.

41:02.043 --> 41:04.034
Who are you to tell me
how to talk to my husband?

41:04.212 --> 41:06.646
You shouldn't push this on him
if he doesn't want to.

41:06.814 --> 41:08.907
I'll push what I want on him.
He's my husband.

41:09.083 --> 41:10.414
I want this apartment.

41:10.585 --> 41:13.611
- Say no, Ted.
- It is amazing that you are still talking.

41:13.788 --> 41:16.052
- Don't listen to her.
- Ted, she's being a tyrant.

41:16.224 --> 41:19.625
She's got your balls on one of those
things that cling back and forth.

41:19.794 --> 41:21.261
- You know?
- Yeah.

41:21.429 --> 41:22.691
- You bitch.
- Brat.

41:22.864 --> 41:23.888
- Shut up!
- You shut up!

41:24.065 --> 41:27.125
No, you shut up!
I will end you, and when I do...

41:27.302 --> 41:29.998
- You know what? I'll tell you...
- No. No. No. Okay, tell me.

41:30.171 --> 41:33.902
He's my husband, I'll talk to him the
way I want to. I'm not living in Brooklyn!

