01:19:58.809 --> 01:20:01.710
- In-laws. I should see them.
- Hmm.

01:20:02.980 --> 01:20:05.608
What's their name? Maybe I know them.

01:20:05.850 --> 01:20:07.283
The Kennedys.

01:20:09.553 --> 01:20:12.147
Not Rose and Martin?

01:20:12.556 --> 01:20:16.219
Yeah. You know them?

01:20:20.631 --> 01:20:23.065
You're not Gerry's Holly?

01:20:23.868 --> 01:20:24.892
What?

01:20:25.236 --> 01:20:26.794
Oh...

01:20:27.404 --> 01:20:29.497
You're the girl from the pub that night.

01:20:30.541 --> 01:20:32.805
I was in Gerry's band.

01:20:32.977 --> 01:20:35.104
Not Billy...

01:20:35.279 --> 01:20:36.541
...Gallagher?
- One and the same.

01:20:36.714 --> 01:20:37.703
[GASPS]

01:20:38.282 --> 01:20:40.307
It's... It's all right.

01:20:40.484 --> 01:20:42.850
It's all right. Me and Gerry,
we shared everything together.

01:20:43.020 --> 01:20:44.282
[GASPS]

01:20:44.455 --> 01:20:47.390
Oh, no, no, no, I didn't mean it like that.

01:20:47.558 --> 01:20:50.755
What I meant was, you know,
he wouldn't have a problem...

01:20:52.029 --> 01:20:54.122
Well, he might have a problem
but, you know...

01:20:54.298 --> 01:20:57.165
...there's not much
he can do about it now, is there?

01:20:59.336 --> 01:21:00.894
Holly.

01:21:01.872 --> 01:21:04.898
Come here. Come back to bed.

01:21:05.943 --> 01:21:08.241
Now, let's... Let's talk.

01:21:11.315 --> 01:21:12.782
Oh...

01:21:13.083 --> 01:21:15.244
I heard he died.

01:21:17.188 --> 01:21:20.385
Tumor, was it? Yeah.

01:21:21.158 --> 01:21:24.423
You know, Gerry and I, we...

01:21:24.595 --> 01:21:28.429
We hadn't seen each other
in a long, long while.

01:21:29.099 --> 01:21:31.624
It's sad when that happens
to best friends, isn't it?

01:21:33.070 --> 01:21:34.059
[SIGHS]

01:21:34.238 --> 01:21:38.106
He... He was a wonderful lad.

01:21:41.345 --> 01:21:43.313
It's all right, you know.

01:21:44.448 --> 01:21:46.211
It's okay.

01:21:46.717 --> 01:21:48.981
You know, these things...

01:21:49.486 --> 01:21:52.046
...they happen now and again.
Not very often...

01:21:52.223 --> 01:21:53.417
[HOLLY CHUCKLES]

01:21:53.624 --> 01:21:55.592
...but now and again.

01:21:59.530 --> 01:22:02.465
Would you like me to tell you
some stories about me and Gerry?

01:22:02.633 --> 01:22:04.567
I've got plenty.

01:22:05.469 --> 01:22:06.868
Yeah?

01:22:07.338 --> 01:22:10.466
Okay, here you go. Come on, sit back.

01:22:15.279 --> 01:22:17.076
You know, he was...

01:22:17.248 --> 01:22:19.682
He was my very, very best mate.

01:22:20.317 --> 01:22:24.913
Starting back when we were terrors
running about at 5 and 6.

01:22:25.122 --> 01:22:26.589
[LAUGHS]

01:22:26.790 --> 01:22:28.849
Oh, he made me laugh.

01:22:29.026 --> 01:22:31.995
There was this time,
I don't remember how old we were...

01:22:32.162 --> 01:22:34.596
...probably, you know, 10, 11.

01:22:35.366 --> 01:22:36.924
We jumped on a train...

01:22:37.101 --> 01:22:38.193
[WILLIAM TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:23:17.808 --> 01:23:19.799
[INAUDIBLE]

01:23:26.917 --> 01:23:28.179
[PIANO PLAYING]

01:23:28.352 --> 01:23:33.119
We received those packages you sent.
Come in. Come in.

01:23:39.129 --> 01:23:40.187
Martin?

01:23:41.832 --> 01:23:43.459
Look who it is.

01:23:43.634 --> 01:23:46.569
Oh, well, look at that.

01:23:46.737 --> 01:23:48.568
Come here, dear.

01:23:48.772 --> 01:23:51.036
So nice to see you.

01:23:51.809 --> 01:23:55.074
He was always one for writing.
Wasn't he?

01:23:55.245 --> 01:23:56.644
Should've gone professional.

01:23:56.814 --> 01:23:59.874
No. He did it for the love of it, Martin.

01:24:00.417 --> 01:24:02.612
Now, where is it?

01:24:02.886 --> 01:24:04.376
Oh, here it is.

01:24:04.555 --> 01:24:08.719
"When Holly visits, take her
to my fort in the back yard...

01:24:08.892 --> 01:24:10.519
...and give her this envelope."

01:24:11.028 --> 01:24:13.622
He knew that I'd come visit you?

01:24:13.931 --> 01:24:17.560
Hmm. Suppose he did. Heh. Martin.

01:24:18.135 --> 01:24:19.568
All right.

01:24:24.008 --> 01:24:27.500
It's not really a fort,
it's just a stone wall.

01:24:27.678 --> 01:24:29.805
He used to call it that when he was little.

01:24:31.982 --> 01:24:34.780
He goes on about other things...

01:24:35.219 --> 01:24:36.743
...lovely things.

01:24:38.789 --> 01:24:43.123
He hadn't much strength in the end
though, did he?

01:24:44.762 --> 01:24:48.425
Makes me sick to think
we weren't there when he died...

01:24:48.599 --> 01:24:49.623
...for the funeral.

01:24:49.800 --> 01:24:52.394
ROSE: But you could hardly walk
just after your operation.

01:24:53.070 --> 01:24:57.268
Maybe you'll come and visit us a bit more
now that he's gone, eh?

01:24:57.508 --> 01:24:59.533
Martin, don't put that on her.

01:24:59.710 --> 01:25:01.871
You're under no obligation.

01:25:02.046 --> 01:25:05.072
It's not like we're blood family.

01:25:05.716 --> 01:25:07.809
I'd like to come visit.

01:25:07.985 --> 01:25:11.853
And I'm sorry we didn't in the past. L...

01:25:12.756 --> 01:25:16.487
I just thought you were angry with me
for taking Gerry away.

01:25:16.660 --> 01:25:19.561
- She wanted you dead, you know.
- Martin, don't you dare!

01:25:19.730 --> 01:25:21.891
No, I don't blame you.

01:25:22.066 --> 01:25:25.502
You know, my mother, she never
quite got over the idea either.

01:25:25.669 --> 01:25:30.163
Yeah, well, you were both so young.
And it happened too fast.

01:25:31.975 --> 01:25:36.537
But Gerry loved you. I saw that.

01:25:37.114 --> 01:25:39.048
I saw that.

01:25:45.255 --> 01:25:48.588
GERRY: To my Galway Girl:
You're an angel for seeing my folks.

01:25:48.759 --> 01:25:53.662
I told you my mom didn't hate your guts.
Well, you know, anymore.

01:25:54.264 --> 01:25:58.724
You are now standing in my fort
where I did all my big thinking.

01:25:58.902 --> 01:26:04.363
This is where I stood thinking about you
after the very first time we met.

01:26:13.784 --> 01:26:16.480
You didn't look real to me at first.

01:26:16.653 --> 01:26:19.520
I never saw so many colors
on one girl before...

01:26:19.690 --> 01:26:22.523
...but you looked like
you belonged out there, all right.

01:26:22.693 --> 01:26:25.025
You and all your colors.

01:26:25.229 --> 01:26:28.357
Do you remember
the first thing you ever said to me?

01:26:28.532 --> 01:26:30.056
I'm lost.

01:26:30.234 --> 01:26:33.601
Oh, you didn't look lost, not to me.

01:26:33.770 --> 01:26:35.965
So, what are you looking for out here?

01:26:36.140 --> 01:26:39.166
Wicklow Mountains National Park?

01:26:39.343 --> 01:26:40.332
[LAUGHS]

01:26:40.511 --> 01:26:44.470
Wicklow Mountains National Park.
Tell me, how long you been walking for?

01:26:44.648 --> 01:26:46.013
A few hours.

01:26:46.183 --> 01:26:50.210
Well, you've probably been in
the national park for a few hours, then.

01:26:50.521 --> 01:26:52.421
Oh, my God.

01:26:52.789 --> 01:26:54.120
This is a park?

01:26:54.291 --> 01:26:55.918
Uh-huh.

01:26:57.494 --> 01:26:58.654
Oh.

01:26:58.829 --> 01:27:00.194
It's so cold!

01:27:00.364 --> 01:27:02.628
The paper said it was gonna be warm.

01:27:02.799 --> 01:27:06.792
It is warm. I know you're lost, but
you do know you're in Ireland, don't you?

01:27:08.705 --> 01:27:11.902
Well, I better head back. Heh.

01:27:12.209 --> 01:27:18.773
- And where is that?
- I'm staying at a B and B in Dunlougahairy.

01:27:18.949 --> 01:27:22.282
Dunlagohairy?
No, I think you mean Dun Laoghaire.

01:27:22.452 --> 01:27:26.320
- Heh-heh. You're kidding?
- No. Would I lie to you?

01:27:27.925 --> 01:27:31.122
- Dun Laoghaire?
- Dun Laoghaire.

01:27:33.297 --> 01:27:36.289
Okay. Thanks.

01:27:36.500 --> 01:27:38.127
You're grand.

01:27:39.303 --> 01:27:41.533
But you're going the wrong way,
you know.

01:27:47.377 --> 01:27:48.605
[SOFTLY]
That way?

01:27:48.779 --> 01:27:50.337
[CHUCKLING]
Okay.

01:27:50.514 --> 01:27:53.506
I think you quite enjoy this getting lost,
don't you?

01:27:54.418 --> 01:27:58.616
You know, actually,
I don't mind so much, not here.

01:27:59.323 --> 01:28:00.813
So how did you come to be here?

01:28:00.991 --> 01:28:04.950
Oh, on my way home, college trip.
We started in Greece.

01:28:05.128 --> 01:28:08.120
Jesus, that's a long walk.
That's a bad joke.

01:28:08.298 --> 01:28:09.629
What are you studying?

01:28:10.834 --> 01:28:12.995
- Art. Yeah.
- Art?

01:28:13.170 --> 01:28:16.628
- Oh, so you're an artist, then?
- Oh. I don't know yet.

01:28:17.074 --> 01:28:18.063
That's great.

01:28:18.242 --> 01:28:19.231
[CHUCKLING]

01:28:19.409 --> 01:28:21.343
Do you make anything or...?

01:28:22.946 --> 01:28:23.935
I don't know yet.

01:28:24.114 --> 01:28:25.138
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

01:28:25.315 --> 01:28:27.112
Well, good luck with that.

01:28:29.853 --> 01:28:31.150
Oh.

01:28:38.562 --> 01:28:40.120
You...

01:28:40.297 --> 01:28:44.461
Would you mind if we walked together
since we're going in the same direction?

01:28:44.635 --> 01:28:48.366
I'll stay on this side of the road.
Don't even have to talk. Just...

01:28:49.206 --> 01:28:53.302
Just quite nice, sometimes walking
along with someone without talking...

01:28:53.477 --> 01:28:56.344
...once you get your feet wet.

01:29:07.958 --> 01:29:09.949
GERRY:
At first, the no-talking thing didn't last.

01:29:10.127 --> 01:29:11.992
Before long, I couldn't get you to shut up.

01:29:12.162 --> 01:29:18.658
But you were so cute, trying to impress me
with William Blake and all your grand plans.

01:29:18.835 --> 01:29:20.996
I had no idea
what you were talking about...

01:29:21.171 --> 01:29:24.072
...but I couldn't help
loving the way you talked.

01:29:24.241 --> 01:29:27.768
"I must create a..."

01:29:28.011 --> 01:29:32.345
Something."...or be enslaved
by another man's..." Something.

01:29:32.516 --> 01:29:35.417
Wait, "I will not...

01:29:35.652 --> 01:29:36.641
[GRUNTS]

01:29:36.820 --> 01:29:40.256
I will not reason or compare.

01:29:40.424 --> 01:29:43.257
My business is to create..."

01:29:43.627 --> 01:29:46.221
- Something. Oh, God.
- Did you just make that up then?

01:29:46.396 --> 01:29:50.059
No, it's William Blake,
but I completely screwed it up.

01:29:50.233 --> 01:29:52.701
No, you didn't, you made it better.
I understood it.

01:29:52.869 --> 01:29:54.336
GERRY:
I didn't have a clue, actually.

01:29:54.504 --> 01:29:59.601
All I know is, if you don't figure out the
"something," you'll just stay ordinary.

01:29:59.776 --> 01:30:05.544
And it doesn't matter if it's a work of art,
or a taco, or a pair of socks.

01:30:05.749 --> 01:30:09.845
Just create something new
and there it is.

01:30:10.020 --> 01:30:13.387
And it's you, out in the world,
outside of you.

01:30:13.557 --> 01:30:17.687
And you can look at it, or hear it,
or read it, or feel it...

01:30:17.861 --> 01:30:20.295
...and you know
a little bit more about you.

01:30:20.464 --> 01:30:23.297
A little bit more than anybody else does.

01:30:23.767 --> 01:30:25.428
Does that make any sense at all?

01:30:27.037 --> 01:30:28.561
Yeah.

01:30:29.139 --> 01:30:30.970
You're saying you want to paint socks.

01:30:32.576 --> 01:30:34.305
Maybe.

01:30:34.478 --> 01:30:35.570
[CHUCKLES]

01:30:35.746 --> 01:30:37.941
GERRY:
I loved you right then and there.

01:30:42.519 --> 01:30:44.749
HOLLY:
Hey, I like this jacket.

01:30:46.056 --> 01:30:48.456
GERRY:
It looks good on you. Got it on a bet.

01:30:48.625 --> 01:30:50.320
- What was the bet?
- Heh.

01:30:51.128 --> 01:30:53.688
I was a few Guinness's
for the worse at this point...

01:30:53.864 --> 01:30:57.061
...but a fella bet me
that I couldn't get a certain girl...

01:30:57.234 --> 01:30:59.429
...to kiss me without a provocation.

01:30:59.603 --> 01:31:02.094
- What girl?
- His girl.

01:31:02.272 --> 01:31:03.967
- Oh! Ha-ha.
- Uh-huh. Ha-ha.

01:31:04.141 --> 01:31:06.974
- How'd you do it?
- There's nothing to it, really.

01:31:07.277 --> 01:31:11.270
A fella just has to tell a woman
the truth without words.

01:31:11.448 --> 01:31:14.212
It's like a signal you send out.

01:31:14.384 --> 01:31:16.375
The woman, she just picks it up.

01:31:17.421 --> 01:31:18.786
And what's the truth?

01:31:20.824 --> 01:31:25.158
That kissing her would be
the end of life as I know it.

01:31:27.264 --> 01:31:28.629
Wow.

01:31:30.133 --> 01:31:32.658
And that's true of every girl
you've gotten to kiss you?

01:31:32.836 --> 01:31:33.996
[GERRY LAUGHS]

01:31:34.371 --> 01:31:37.670
I could turn it on and off when I was
younger and I had no principles.

01:31:37.841 --> 01:31:43.040
When every girl that I was lucky enough
to kiss was the end of life as I knew it.

01:31:45.449 --> 01:31:46.882
And now?

01:31:49.152 --> 01:31:53.782
Now I only send it out when I think
she might be the one that makes it true.

01:32:03.433 --> 01:32:06.425
I know where I am now.
Thanks, it was really nice to meet you.

01:32:06.603 --> 01:32:09.037
- No, I could walk you into town.
- Oh, no, it's okay.

01:32:09.206 --> 01:32:12.141
I know where I am.
I know where I'm going.

01:32:16.213 --> 01:32:18.044
I'll never forget this.

01:32:23.119 --> 01:32:24.347
Your jacket.

01:32:24.521 --> 01:32:26.512
[DOG BARKING]

01:32:28.058 --> 01:32:29.457
No, wait!

01:32:29.626 --> 01:32:31.093
[WHISPERING]
Wait, wait, don't move.

01:32:31.261 --> 01:32:34.025
- What?
- Oh, yeah, it's a wild Irish dog.

01:32:34.197 --> 01:32:35.186
- A what?
- Shh!

01:32:36.266 --> 01:32:38.200
- You have to stand still.
- Okay.

01:32:38.368 --> 01:32:42.532
Get close, like one person.

01:32:42.706 --> 01:32:45.607
And if we separate, he'll feel...

01:32:45.775 --> 01:32:48.369
...threatened and attack our vital parts.

01:32:48.545 --> 01:32:51.446
- What vital parts? All my parts are vital.
- Shh, shh.

01:32:51.748 --> 01:32:53.739
[BARKING THEN GROWLING]

01:32:54.351 --> 01:32:55.784
GERRY:
We have to stand still.

01:32:55.952 --> 01:32:58.785
Now, just let him sniff around a bit.

01:32:59.089 --> 01:33:00.113
[SNIFFING]

01:33:01.324 --> 01:33:02.621
GERRY:
Now wait.

01:33:11.368 --> 01:33:13.427
[WHISPERING]
I'm really scared.

01:33:13.603 --> 01:33:15.594
Would you put
your arms around me?

01:33:15.772 --> 01:33:17.137
All right.

01:33:17.307 --> 01:33:20.071
- Yeah, that's probably a good idea.
- Yeah.

01:33:20.243 --> 01:33:21.710
[DOG PANTING]

01:33:21.878 --> 01:33:26.508
Do you think we could turn around and
face each other without freaking him out?

01:33:27.551 --> 01:33:30.952
Ahh... Okay. Sure.

01:33:31.154 --> 01:33:34.146
- But let's move very slowly, okay?
- Okay.

01:33:40.931 --> 01:33:42.023
- Ow.
- Oh, sorry.

01:33:42.198 --> 01:33:44.758
I haven't done this in a while.

01:33:44.935 --> 01:33:47.995
I've been seeing this boy,
but we don't do much. I don't know why.

01:33:48.305 --> 01:33:51.706
- Maybe it's me.
- No, he's a boy who...

01:33:53.443 --> 01:33:56.037
...doesn't know anything about kissing.

01:33:57.080 --> 01:33:58.547
That's a man's business.

01:33:59.583 --> 01:34:01.141
Is it?

01:34:23.740 --> 01:34:26.675
That was the most perfect...

01:34:28.345 --> 01:34:30.506
...perfect first kiss.

01:34:31.715 --> 01:34:33.979
That was the second.

01:34:34.284 --> 01:34:35.581
This is the third.

01:34:58.742 --> 01:35:00.539
MAN:
Brody, come.

01:35:00.944 --> 01:35:01.933
Hey, Gerry.

01:35:02.712 --> 01:35:04.543
Yeah. How are you, Jeff?

01:35:07.250 --> 01:35:10.617
- Hey, where you going?
- No, stay. Stay.

01:35:10.787 --> 01:35:13.017
No, but... You have my jacket.

01:35:13.189 --> 01:35:16.352
I know, I'm keeping it
unless we meet again.

01:35:16.660 --> 01:35:17.957
I bet we do.

01:35:18.128 --> 01:35:20.426
That's a bet you're gonna
have to win because...

01:35:20.597 --> 01:35:23.862
...if we do meet again then that'll be
the end of it, you know.

01:35:24.668 --> 01:35:25.794
The end of what?

01:35:26.302 --> 01:35:27.735
Life as we know it.

01:35:27.971 --> 01:35:29.165
[CHUCKLES]

01:35:30.240 --> 01:35:33.505
- Look, I'm singing at this pub...
- No, no, no. Don't tell me.

01:35:33.677 --> 01:35:36.475
If I happen to walk into the right one
in the right town...

01:35:36.646 --> 01:35:39.911
...then we'll know for sure, won't we?
And if I don't...

01:35:40.083 --> 01:35:44.076
...then that'll just be the most perfect kiss
ever created by two strangers...

01:35:44.254 --> 01:35:47.155
...and we'll just keep it perfect
for the rest of our lives.

01:35:47.624 --> 01:35:49.615
- What's your name?
- No, no! Wait, no, don't.

01:35:49.793 --> 01:35:51.886
Don't, don't. No, no...

01:35:56.833 --> 01:35:59.165
GERRY:
Life had changed as I knew it.

01:35:59.736 --> 01:36:02.364
And now it's changed again, luv.

01:36:02.539 --> 01:36:05.372
See, I don't worry about you
remembering me...

01:36:05.542 --> 01:36:09.103
...it's that girl on the road
you keep forgetting.

01:36:09.279 --> 01:36:12.908
"My business is to create.

01:36:13.683 --> 01:36:16.083
It doesn't even matter what you do."

01:36:16.653 --> 01:36:19.053
You told me that, remember.

01:36:21.925 --> 01:36:23.517
P.S.

01:36:34.738 --> 01:36:37.639
GERRY:
So go home. Go find it.

01:36:37.807 --> 01:36:41.402
Find that thing
that makes you like nobody else.

01:36:41.578 --> 01:36:43.136
I'll help.

01:36:43.313 --> 01:36:45.247
Look for a sign.

01:36:45.415 --> 01:36:46.814
[PHONE RINGING]

01:36:46.983 --> 01:36:48.007
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

01:36:48.184 --> 01:36:50.812
PATRICIA [OVER MACHINE]: It's Mom.
Sharon called, said you're home.

01:36:50.987 --> 01:36:52.386
SHARON: Where are you?
PATRICIA: Call me.

01:36:52.555 --> 01:36:55.786
SHARON: You haven't returned my calls.
Come to my first baby doctor's appointment.

01:36:55.959 --> 01:36:58.018
DENISE: What is going on?
Nobody's heard from you...

01:36:58.194 --> 01:37:00.094
...my maid of honor. Call me.
SHARON: Call me.

01:37:00.263 --> 01:37:04.529
GERRY: If you need to find any job
to get by, be realistic, luv, all right?

01:37:04.701 --> 01:37:06.896
DENISE: I cannot believe
you are not calling me back!

01:37:07.070 --> 01:37:08.833
GERRY:
You can't be a secret agent...

01:37:09.005 --> 01:37:11.064
...and there's no such thing
as a vampire slayer.

01:37:11.241 --> 01:37:14.005
DENISE: I'm getting married. Where are you?
SHARON: Pick up the phone!

01:37:14.177 --> 01:37:16.008
PATRICIA:
His death is a part of your life now.

01:37:16.179 --> 01:37:17.237
DENISE:
I am so mad at you!

01:37:17.413 --> 01:37:19.404
[TV PLAYING]

01:37:22.485 --> 01:37:24.544
[OVER TV]
Shh. There she is.

01:37:32.428 --> 01:37:33.588
[STOPS FILM]

01:37:37.200 --> 01:37:38.997
Great shoes.

01:37:39.235 --> 01:37:42.227
[PHONE RINGING]

01:37:44.574 --> 01:37:45.563
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

01:37:45.742 --> 01:37:47.801
DENISE:
Okay, this message is for Holly Kennedy.

01:37:47.977 --> 01:37:49.672
Please tell her, her friend Denise...

01:37:49.846 --> 01:37:53.680
...is getting married December 31 st
and she's not invited. Okay?

01:37:53.850 --> 01:37:55.909
How about that? You're not invited.

01:39:30.213 --> 01:39:31.646
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:39:31.814 --> 01:39:34.180
DENISE:
Look at this. It needs to be tighter!

01:39:34.350 --> 01:39:36.443
WOMAN:
All right, I will do whatever you want...

01:39:36.619 --> 01:39:38.484
...but I'm not so sure, I mean, I think...

01:39:38.655 --> 01:39:42.523
No, listen, your bust looks absolutely right,
because let me tell you something...

01:39:42.692 --> 01:39:45.160
...you don't want to look too busty.

01:39:45.328 --> 01:39:49.321
Yeah, well, see, although, you know,
my breasts are beautiful and firm...

01:39:49.499 --> 01:39:53.663
...they do often have a mind of their own
and they can go off in different directions...

01:39:53.836 --> 01:39:55.827
...without adult supervision.

01:39:56.005 --> 01:39:59.031
So could you please just take it in just
a quarter-inch? Just a quarter-inch.

01:39:59.208 --> 01:40:00.402
- Okay.
- Okay.

01:40:05.615 --> 01:40:09.107
Could you give us...
Excuse us for a minute, please?

01:40:09.285 --> 01:40:11.116
- Sure.
- Thanks.

01:40:16.960 --> 01:40:18.689
You look beautiful.

01:40:19.629 --> 01:40:21.358
Well, I could've used some help.

01:40:21.898 --> 01:40:26.164
This is the twelfth dress
I've tried on. So...

01:40:28.004 --> 01:40:29.164
I'm sorry.

01:40:30.139 --> 01:40:34.166
Well, you were supposed to be my maid of
honor, but of course I didn't hear from you.

01:40:35.712 --> 01:40:39.705
Sharon feels too conspicuous since
she's popped. So, guess what?

01:40:39.882 --> 01:40:42.043
I had to ask Tom's 51 -year-old sister...

01:40:42.218 --> 01:40:45.051
...who looks like Jerry Springer
and doesn't like me...

01:40:47.390 --> 01:40:50.723
...all because my best friend couldn't
stand me being so happy.

01:40:51.494 --> 01:40:52.984
Why? Why is that?

01:40:53.162 --> 01:40:57.428
Because our lives were moving on and you
weren't the center of attention anymore?

01:40:57.600 --> 01:40:59.227
- Yes.
- Really?

01:40:59.402 --> 01:41:02.633
- It was awful and I'm really sorry.
- Oh, no, I'm so sorry, honey.

01:41:02.805 --> 01:41:03.931
No, I'm so sorry.

01:41:04.107 --> 01:41:05.699
You were right and I was wrong.

01:41:05.875 --> 01:41:08.867
God, I'm such a bitch! I'm sorry!
I was so crazy mad.

01:41:09.045 --> 01:41:10.478
I hope you can forgive me.

01:41:10.646 --> 01:41:14.605
Oh, you know what, it's not too late.
You can still be a bridesmaid with Sharon.

01:41:15.451 --> 01:41:17.078
- Okay.
- Okay?

01:41:17.787 --> 01:41:19.721
Can I ask you a favor?

01:41:20.923 --> 01:41:24.086
- I want to make your wedding shoes.
- My shoes?

01:41:24.260 --> 01:41:26.194
What'd you turn into, Geppetto?

01:41:26.362 --> 01:41:29.263
Oh, my God! These are gorgeous!

01:41:29.432 --> 01:41:33.664
I've been taking a class. It just happened
out of the blue. I really love it.

01:41:33.836 --> 01:41:35.303
Oh, my God!

01:41:35.805 --> 01:41:37.397
HOLLY:
They're one-of-a-kind.

01:41:37.573 --> 01:41:39.973
You'll be the only bride in history
to wear them.

01:41:40.143 --> 01:41:41.132
Love that!

01:41:42.245 --> 01:41:44.440
Oh, God, Holly!

01:41:44.614 --> 01:41:46.980
This is like shoe art.

01:41:47.150 --> 01:41:51.052
They're gorgeous! We have to
show these to someone.

01:41:52.855 --> 01:41:53.844
[CAR HORN HONKS]

01:41:54.023 --> 01:41:56.116
HOLLY:
I feel like Gerry's guiding me.

01:41:56.292 --> 01:41:59.955
I mean, shoes! I love shoes but I never
thought about it.

01:42:00.129 --> 01:42:01.460
You look so great.

01:42:01.631 --> 01:42:02.928
Thanks.

01:42:03.099 --> 01:42:05.693
- Course, I look great too, right? Ha-ha.
- Yes.

01:42:05.868 --> 01:42:09.429
When all this started happening,
you're the first person I wanted to tell.

01:42:09.605 --> 01:42:10.833
Isn't that funny?

01:42:11.007 --> 01:42:14.636
That's hilarious. Any way we can stretch
this lunch out into a dinner?

01:42:15.645 --> 01:42:17.340
I'm going to change the subject.

01:42:19.115 --> 01:42:22.482
- How are you?
- I'm good. Things are good.

01:42:23.286 --> 01:42:27.154
I've got some, some ideas for the future,
some possible business prospects.

01:42:27.323 --> 01:42:29.086
I think about you all the time.

01:42:31.494 --> 01:42:33.587
That's a little too much information,
I guess.

01:42:33.763 --> 01:42:34.787
Yes.

01:42:34.964 --> 01:42:36.625
But you did say you were
thinking about me.

01:42:37.166 --> 01:42:39.691
Because you've been a real friend
through this all.

01:42:40.770 --> 01:42:44.399
So, you haven't thought about me
in the nude?

01:42:44.874 --> 01:42:46.171
No.

01:42:46.676 --> 01:42:47.973
- Not once?
- No.

01:42:48.144 --> 01:42:50.408
- Not even without my shirt?
- Gerry, stop it!

01:42:52.348 --> 01:42:53.372
Daniel.

01:42:59.722 --> 01:43:00.984
I'm Daniel.

01:43:03.860 --> 01:43:04.918
Sorry.

01:43:08.364 --> 01:43:11.356
You think you'll ever feel about
somebody the way you felt about Gerry...

01:43:11.567 --> 01:43:14.229
...or do you have to wait for a letter
to figure that out?

01:43:16.639 --> 01:43:17.901
Where you going?

01:43:22.912 --> 01:43:24.470
I really like you...

01:43:25.815 --> 01:43:28.716
...but I can't be the invisible man.

01:43:29.819 --> 01:43:32.219
I'm tired of being the shoulder.

01:43:34.323 --> 01:43:39.090
I want to be another body part you need,
you know? I wanna be...

01:43:39.262 --> 01:43:42.060
...the bad guy.
I want a woman to go crazy over me...

01:43:42.231 --> 01:43:46.725
...and then I wanna use her up
until she's ruined for all other men.

01:43:46.903 --> 01:43:51.363
- You don't wanna do that.
- No, I don't wanna do that, but I would...

01:43:52.208 --> 01:43:53.197
[SIGHS]

01:43:53.376 --> 01:43:56.834
I'd like to date a woman
who actually likes men.

01:44:03.519 --> 01:44:05.714
I'd like to be somebody's Gerry.

01:44:16.365 --> 01:44:20.802
It's all right.
Honestly, it's not your fault, it's mine.

01:44:23.105 --> 01:44:26.006
I didn't plan on feeling something for you,
it just sort of happened.

01:44:26.175 --> 01:44:27.574
So I'm sorry about that.

01:44:36.552 --> 01:44:38.144
Is your guest coming back?

01:44:39.488 --> 01:44:42.150
- No.
- Just you on your own, then?

01:45:06.349 --> 01:45:08.340
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

01:46:09.779 --> 01:46:11.110
Take a break, will you?

01:46:12.882 --> 01:46:15.214
- Mom!
- What's the matter?

01:46:18.554 --> 01:46:19.851
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

01:46:20.022 --> 01:46:22.013
[SOBBING]

01:46:23.092 --> 01:46:24.719
Come on.

01:46:25.594 --> 01:46:27.221
Come on.

01:46:27.697 --> 01:46:29.562
What happened?

01:46:30.833 --> 01:46:34.166
When... When Daddy left...

01:46:35.004 --> 01:46:38.098
...I was 14 and I said:

01:46:38.307 --> 01:46:41.799
"That's it, never again. No man..."

01:46:43.913 --> 01:46:45.437
And then I meet Gerry.

01:46:50.853 --> 01:46:55.517
This wonderful man happens to me
and then... And then...

01:46:55.691 --> 01:46:57.556
And then he died!

01:46:57.727 --> 01:46:59.558
- What was the point?
- I know, honey.

01:46:59.729 --> 01:47:02.425
I'm so angry I could kill somebody!

01:47:02.598 --> 01:47:04.566
I'm alone and...

01:47:04.867 --> 01:47:08.598
...it doesn't matter what job I have,
or what I do or what I don't do...

01:47:08.771 --> 01:47:11.171
...or what friends I have. He's not here.

01:47:11.340 --> 01:47:14.571
I'm... I'm not here.

01:47:15.344 --> 01:47:19.144
- I mean, you're alone no matter what.
- That's right.

01:47:19.415 --> 01:47:21.406
[SOBBING]

01:47:21.817 --> 01:47:26.015
You know, I didn't come here for you
to give me some bullshit honest answer.

01:47:26.188 --> 01:47:28.349
Why can't you lie to me just once?

01:47:28.524 --> 01:47:30.253
I'm sorry, sweetheart.

01:47:35.698 --> 01:47:40.101
- I can't breathe. I can't breathe.
- Shh. Come on.

01:47:41.537 --> 01:47:43.505
Let's go for a walk.

01:47:45.408 --> 01:47:47.603
PATRICIA:
Your father and I used to come here.

01:47:47.777 --> 01:47:49.142
They had dances.

01:47:49.311 --> 01:47:51.245
Well, not really dances.

01:47:51.414 --> 01:47:54.247
We'd come with radios and cigarettes...

01:47:54.417 --> 01:47:57.250
...and drink beer and listen to Jimi Hendrix.

01:47:59.855 --> 01:48:04.087
I bet you've had a hard time walking into
a room full of people on your own, right?

01:48:05.161 --> 01:48:06.992
Yeah, I know that.

01:48:07.930 --> 01:48:12.333
I know what it is not to feel like you're in
the room until he looks at you...

01:48:12.501 --> 01:48:16.665
...or touches your hand, or even makes
a joke at your expense...

01:48:17.306 --> 01:48:19.774
...just to let everyone know
you're with him.

01:48:20.543 --> 01:48:22.101
You're his.

01:48:24.146 --> 01:48:26.205
God, that man could make me laugh.

01:48:28.017 --> 01:48:29.348
Daddy?

01:48:29.518 --> 01:48:31.383
[LAUGHING]

01:48:31.554 --> 01:48:33.784
I don't ever remember you laughing.

01:48:37.526 --> 01:48:40.359
Well, that makes me sad...

01:48:43.566 --> 01:48:45.500
...because I did.

01:48:48.237 --> 01:48:49.966
I did.

01:48:55.478 --> 01:48:58.914
Did you hate Gerry because
he reminded you of Dad?

01:49:00.716 --> 01:49:02.411
A little.

01:49:05.721 --> 01:49:07.086
[SIGHS]

01:49:07.656 --> 01:49:12.150
You know the worst thing for a parent,
second after losing a child?

01:49:13.696 --> 01:49:17.188
Watching your child head for
the same life you had...

01:49:18.100 --> 01:49:20.159
...and you can't stop it.

01:49:23.072 --> 01:49:26.166
It's a terrible, helpless feeling.

01:49:27.443 --> 01:49:29.741
Makes you angry all the time...

01:49:31.180 --> 01:49:33.148
...and I've been angry...

01:49:34.450 --> 01:49:36.782
...a very long time.

01:49:38.754 --> 01:49:39.743
[SIGHS]

01:49:39.922 --> 01:49:40.980
I'm exhausted.

01:49:45.961 --> 01:49:47.986
Do you think we'll ever see Dad again?

01:49:49.865 --> 01:49:51.628
No, sweetheart.

01:49:52.868 --> 01:49:54.495
Never.

01:49:57.806 --> 01:50:00.138
So you have to stop waiting.

01:50:24.800 --> 01:50:25.960
You?

01:50:28.604 --> 01:50:32.836
I have to say I was impressed by how
he worked everything out ahead of time...

01:50:33.876 --> 01:50:36.868
...every delivery schedule,
the mailbox key...

01:50:38.347 --> 01:50:41.316
Getting that leather jacket out
of your apartment wasn't easy...

01:50:41.483 --> 01:50:43.815
...with you acting like Miss Havisham.

01:50:48.424 --> 01:50:50.153
He made me promise.

01:50:51.126 --> 01:50:52.821
I couldn't say no.

01:50:53.529 --> 01:50:57.522
I told him I didn't think
it was good for you, but...

01:50:58.200 --> 01:51:00.031
...I couldn't say no.

01:51:04.373 --> 01:51:06.000
It's the last one...

01:51:10.980 --> 01:51:12.845
...so all alone or not...

01:51:14.316 --> 01:51:16.181
...you gotta walk ahead.

01:51:21.056 --> 01:51:23.115
Thing to remember is...

01:51:23.859 --> 01:51:28.853
...if we're all alone,
then we're all together in that too.

01:51:31.667 --> 01:51:34.135
It helps me sometimes.

01:52:35.330 --> 01:52:36.388
[ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS]

01:52:36.565 --> 01:52:39.125
DANIEL [OVER MACHINE]:
Hi, it's Daniel.

01:52:39.301 --> 01:52:43.601
Remember what I said in the restaurant?
Well, please forget it word by word.

01:52:45.040 --> 01:52:47.406
They're gonna build
a new Yankee stadium.

01:52:48.277 --> 01:52:51.644
I don't know why I said that.
I'm making small talk. I hate small talk.

01:52:51.814 --> 01:52:56.251
I hate the people who make small talk.
I should... I should stop. I'm stopping.

01:52:56.418 --> 01:52:57.407
Shit!

01:52:57.586 --> 01:52:59.076
[HANGS UP]

01:53:08.931 --> 01:53:10.523
Gerry?

01:53:14.903 --> 01:53:15.892
[FOOTSTEPS]

01:53:16.071 --> 01:53:18.904
DANIEL:
My uncle can get us in anytime we want.

01:53:19.575 --> 01:53:21.736
He turned the lights on for us.

01:53:24.346 --> 01:53:26.177
HOLLY:
It's amazing...

01:53:53.709 --> 01:53:55.074
You sure?

01:53:57.112 --> 01:53:58.841
It's okay.

01:54:00.549 --> 01:54:04.110
DANIEL:
"Dear Holly, I don't have much time.

01:54:04.520 --> 01:54:09.457
I don't mean literally, I mean, you're out
buying ice cream and you'll be home soon...

01:54:09.858 --> 01:54:12.383
...but I have a feeling this is the last letter.

01:54:12.561 --> 01:54:15.155
Because there's only one thing
left to tell you.

01:54:15.731 --> 01:54:18.791
It isn't to go down memory lane
or make you buy a lamp.

01:54:18.967 --> 01:54:22.130
You can take care of yourself
without any help from me.

01:54:23.272 --> 01:54:28.141
It's to tell you how much you move me.
How you changed me.

01:54:28.911 --> 01:54:32.244
You made me a man
by loving me, Holly...

01:54:32.414 --> 01:54:36.009
...and for that I am eternally grateful.

01:54:36.185 --> 01:54:37.584
Literally.

01:54:38.821 --> 01:54:43.155
If you can promise me anything,
promise me that whenever you're sad...

01:54:43.325 --> 01:54:44.724
...or unsure...

01:54:45.394 --> 01:54:47.726
...or you lose complete faith...

01:54:48.497 --> 01:54:51.432
...that you'll try and see yourself
through my eyes.

01:54:51.934 --> 01:54:54.835
Thank you for the honor
of being my wife.

01:54:55.037 --> 01:54:57.335
I'm a man with no regrets.

01:54:57.506 --> 01:54:59.030
How lucky am I?

01:55:00.409 --> 01:55:05.073
You made my life, Holly,
but I'm just one chapter in yours.

01:55:05.447 --> 01:55:07.210
There'll be more.

01:55:07.683 --> 01:55:09.173
I promise.

01:55:10.185 --> 01:55:13.245
So here it comes, the big one.

01:55:15.190 --> 01:55:17.283
Don't be afraid to fall in love again.

01:55:18.894 --> 01:55:22.694
Watch out for that signal
when life as you know it ends.

01:55:25.000 --> 01:55:29.437
P.S., I will always love you."

01:55:49.925 --> 01:55:52.325
Have you thought about this?

01:55:53.495 --> 01:55:55.725
About me, I mean?

01:55:57.900 --> 01:55:59.561
Have you?

01:56:02.638 --> 01:56:04.265
Yeah.

01:56:29.965 --> 01:56:32.229
- This isn't gonna work, is it?
- No way, no how!

01:56:32.401 --> 01:56:33.561
- Damn!
- Oh!

01:56:33.835 --> 01:56:35.598
[LAUGHING]

01:56:35.804 --> 01:56:37.431
Oh, wow.

01:56:37.839 --> 01:56:40.330
I mean, that was like kissing my sister.

01:56:40.509 --> 01:56:43.171
- I'm so relieved!
- Ha-ha-ha.

01:56:43.345 --> 01:56:46.906
I got this letter and I thought he must have
been feeling self-sacrificing...

01:56:47.082 --> 01:56:50.074
...but he's really full of crap.
If he meant it, he'd give me a sign.

01:56:50.252 --> 01:56:53.483
- I hate signs.
- Then I got your message on the machine.

01:56:53.755 --> 01:56:55.154
[SIGHS]

01:57:00.028 --> 01:57:02.758
Weird, bitter friends?

01:57:04.533 --> 01:57:06.296
Forever.

01:57:06.935 --> 01:57:08.368
[SIGHS]

01:57:18.413 --> 01:57:20.176
What's wrong, friend?

01:57:20.349 --> 01:57:22.317
It's Gerry.

01:57:24.319 --> 01:57:26.150
It's been a year...

01:57:28.490 --> 01:57:31.357
...and I don't feel him
around me anymore.

01:57:33.362 --> 01:57:35.660
I don't think he's here anymore.

01:57:38.166 --> 01:57:40.361
I think Gerry's gone.

01:57:41.903 --> 01:57:43.530
[WHISPERS]
He's really gone.

01:58:02.791 --> 01:58:05.225
HOLLY:
Dear Gerry, you said you wanted me...

01:58:05.394 --> 01:58:06.827
...to fall in love again...

01:58:06.995 --> 01:58:11.398
...and maybe one day I will,
but there are all kinds of love out there.

01:58:12.601 --> 01:58:14.398
This is my one and only life...

01:58:14.803 --> 01:58:18.261
...and it's a great and terrible
and short and endless thing...

01:58:18.440 --> 01:58:21.238
...and none of us come out of it alive.

01:58:31.086 --> 01:58:35.716
I don't have a plan except
that it's time my mom laughed again.

01:58:35.924 --> 01:58:37.755
She's never seen the world.

01:58:37.926 --> 01:58:43.922
She's never seen Ireland, so I'm
taking her back to where we started.

01:58:50.172 --> 01:58:52.538
Maybe now she'll understand.

01:59:01.083 --> 01:59:02.277
Mom?

01:59:17.866 --> 01:59:19.060
William?

01:59:20.969 --> 01:59:22.163
Hello, you.

01:59:25.474 --> 01:59:26.839
You back for another visit?

01:59:28.176 --> 01:59:29.473
How long?

01:59:30.545 --> 01:59:32.103
I don't know.

01:59:34.416 --> 01:59:36.782
Oh, um... This is my mom, Patricia.

01:59:37.219 --> 01:59:39.084
Hello. This is me father, Patsy.

01:59:43.325 --> 01:59:45.190
You've dropped your sweets, luv.

01:59:45.360 --> 01:59:47.351
Mustn't do that around these parts.

01:59:47.529 --> 01:59:51.124
Pretty woman like you,
a fella could take it the wrong way.

01:59:51.633 --> 01:59:52.691
[LAUGHING]

01:59:52.868 --> 01:59:54.859
[PATSY LAUGHING]

02:00:09.117 --> 02:00:10.675
So I'll see you around, then?

02:00:11.753 --> 02:00:13.186
Yeah.

02:00:19.994 --> 02:00:23.896
HOLLY: I don't know how you did it,
but you brought me back from the dead.

02:00:24.064 --> 02:00:26.089
I'll write to you again soon.

02:00:26.266 --> 02:00:28.131
P. S...

02:00:28.302 --> 02:00:29.963
[WHISPERS]
Guess what.

02:06:00.030 --> 02:06:01.021
{{{the end}}}
